NS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\\n- [Attempt 1] Build fails due to API incompatibility between cryptofuzz and Botan library. cryptofuzz expects Botan::Invalid_Argument exception type and complete definitions of EC_AffinePoint/EC_Group classes, but these are missing or have different names in current Botan version. Code also uses many deprecated Botan APIs.\\n- [Attempt 1] Initial setup revealed Botan API compatibility issues. The cryptofuzz codebase expects Botan::Invalid_Argument exception type and specific EC classes that appear to be missing or have different APIs in the Botan version being used. This is a library version mismatch problem rather than the original JSON literal operator issue.\\n- [Attempt 1] Fundamental configuration error: The build expects relic toolkit at /src/relic/ but we\'re mounting cryptofuzz there. The Dockerfile clones relic, botan, and cryptofuzz separately, but the mount path is incorrect. This is a catastrophic misconfiguration where we\'re trying to build the wrong project in the wrong location.\\n\\n\\n--- Configuration Files (Dockerfile, build.sh, etc.) ---\\n\\n### Content from: Dockerfile ###\\n# Copyright 2021 Google LLC\\n#\\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \\"License\\");\\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\\n#\\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\\n#\\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an \\"AS IS\\" BASIS,\\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\\n# limitations under the License.\\n#\\n################################################################################\\n\\nFROM gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder@sha256:3f5877c3af4e971e79b6b0530aebaaabc262c3a7a2f858cf0ca33a2f34d5711b\\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y make autoconf automake libtool wget python\\nRUN git clone  https://github.com/relic-toolkit/relic.git\\nRUN git clone  https://github.com/randombit/botan.git\\nRUN git clone  https://github.com/MozillaSecurity/cryptofuzz\\nRUN wget https://archives.boost.io/release/1.84.0/source/boost_1_84_0.tar.bz2\\nCOPY build.sh $SRC/\\n# This is to fix Fuzz Introspector build by using LLVM old pass manager\\n# re https://github.com/ossf/fuzz-introspector/issues/305\\nENV OLD_LLVMPASS 1\\n\\n### Content from: build.sh ###\\n#!/bin/bash -eu\\n# Copyright 2021 Google LLC\\n#\\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \\"License\\");\\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\\n#\\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\\n#\\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an \\"AS IS\\" BASIS,\\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\\n# limitations under the License.\\n#\\n################################################################################\\n\\nexport CXXFLAGS=\\"$CXXFLAGS -DCRYPTOFUZZ_NO_OPENSSL\\"\\nexport LIBFUZZER_LINK=\\"$LIB_FUZZING_ENGINE\\"\\n\\n# Install Boost headers\\ncd $SRC/\\ntar jxf boost_1_84_0.tar.bz2\\ncd boost_1_84_0/\\nCFLAGS=\\"\\" CXXFLAGS=\\"\\" ./bootstrap.sh\\nCFLAGS=\\"\\" CXXFLAGS=\\"\\" ./b2 headers\\ncp -R boost/ /usr/include/\\n\\n# Build Relic\\ncd $SRC/relic/\\nmkdir build/\\ncd build/\\nif [[ $CFLAGS = *-m32* ]]\\nthen\\n    export RELIC_ARCH=\\"X86\\"\\nelse\\n    export RELIC_ARCH=\\"X64\\"\\nfi\\ncmake .. -DCOMP=\\"$CFLAGS\\" -DQUIET=on -DRAND=CALL -DSHLIB=off -DSTBIN=off -DTESTS=0 -DBENCH=0 -DALLOC=DYNAMIC -DARCH=$RELIC_ARCH\\nmake -j$(nproc)\\ncd ../..\\nexport RELIC_PATH=$(realpath relic)\\nexport CXXFLAGS=\\"$CXXFLAGS -DCRYPTOFUZZ_RELIC\\"\\n\\n# Build Bot